12:18.571 --> 12:20.698
- Stop trying to get
your life right through me!

12:20.781 --> 12:24.368
{\an1}- Oh, okay, Ms. Feldman's
gonna tell you a story

12:24.452 --> 12:27.538
{\an1}about a college otter
who got tweaked out on courage

12:27.621 --> 12:29.290
{\an1}and got a little bit
too mouthy!

12:29.373 --> 12:31.375
- You already wasted
my time with this.

12:31.459 --> 12:33.878
- Ah...zip it!

12:33.961 --> 12:36.297
{\an1}Once there was
a formerly shy otter

12:36.380 --> 12:39.133
{\an1}who followed a band
by the name of Phish.

12:39.216 --> 12:41.260
{\an1}By the time Phish
was headlining Bonnaroo,

12:41.343 --> 12:45.681
{\an1}she decided that nobody was
a better Phish fan than she was.

12:45.764 --> 12:48.851
And after a heated argument
on whether or not the band

12:48.934 --> 12:51.729
{\an1}had sold out
by doing stadium shows,

12:51.812 --> 12:54.648
{\an1}she ripped off
an antenna from a VW bus

12:54.732 --> 12:57.943
{\an1}and whipped a fake,
white Rasta otter with it

12:58.027 --> 13:01.155
until he was really,
really, really hurt.

13:01.238 --> 13:03.324
But what she didn't know was,

13:03.407 --> 13:07.161
{\an1}that otter was
an undercover narcotics officer.

13:07.244 --> 13:09.914
{\an1}Mm-hmm.
She ended up in jail.

13:09.997 --> 13:11.540
A prison otter's bitch.

13:11.624 --> 13:13.709
{\an1}And all that
could have been avoided

13:13.792 --> 13:16.378
{\an1}if she hadn't used
her otter voice to be

13:16.462 --> 13:20.049
{\an1}such a rotten little a-hole
to the other otters.

13:20.132 --> 13:21.842
{\an1}The end.

13:21.926 --> 13:24.845
{\an3}- I don't want to be
a prison otter's bitch!

13:24.929 --> 13:27.556
{\an3}I'm sorry!

13:27.640 --> 13:30.601
<i>[rock music]</i>

13:30.684 --> 13:34.855
♪ ♪

13:34.939 --> 13:37.983
- Bloostery, Ember,
we need to make sure

13:38.067 --> 13:40.569
{\an3}there are water stations
at every mile mark.

13:40.653 --> 13:43.572
{\an1}- Hi! You must be members
of Deb's coven.

13:43.656 --> 13:44.615
{\an1}I want to thank you
for canonizing our march

13:44.698 --> 13:46.742
with your sacred invocations.

13:46.825 --> 13:49.745
{\an3}- I bribed them
with the nacho waterfall.

13:49.828 --> 13:50.955
{\an3}Get on it!

13:51.038 --> 13:52.873
{\an3}We can't have
dehydrated marchers!

13:52.957 --> 13:55.793
{\an3}Into the night,
my little ravens!

13:55.876 --> 13:57.211
- Great turnout.

13:57.294 --> 13:59.088
{\an1}You would not believe
how many cute guys

13:59.171 --> 14:00.714
{\an1}support a woman's right
to dress like a ho.

14:00.798 --> 14:03.092
- Yes!
- Check out my shirt.

14:03.175 --> 14:06.136
[laughs] It's puff paint!
I made it myself.

14:06.220 --> 14:08.514
- Cool. I made one too.

14:08.597 --> 14:10.015
<i>- Great!</i>
<i>We're all here.</i>

14:10.099 --> 14:11.892
Let's get this march started.

14:14.186 --> 14:15.938
Ladies and gentlemen!

14:16.021 --> 14:19.608
Tonight we are taking back
the twat!

14:19.692 --> 14:21.819
Before we march,
I'd like to invite the woman

14:21.902 --> 14:24.280
who started this all
to say a few words.

14:24.363 --> 14:26.657
Chelsea Snap!

14:29.535 --> 14:30.703
Chelsea?

14:30.786 --> 14:33.455
<i>[opera music]</i>

14:33.539 --> 14:34.957
{\an1}- Ma'am, that's sold
by the ounce.

14:35.040 --> 14:36.959
It's not complimentary.

14:37.042 --> 14:39.128
- Go fuck yourself.

14:39.211 --> 14:41.046
- I'm sure she'll be here
any second.

14:41.130 --> 14:43.299
So everybody knows the plan.

14:43.382 --> 14:44.633
We'll be marching
through the streets

14:44.717 --> 14:46.468
to the Board of Education.

14:46.552 --> 14:52.349
We are going to overcome
this oppression!

14:52.433 --> 14:54.101
[crowd gasps]

14:54.184 --> 14:55.352
- Isn't this a little much?

14:55.436 --> 14:57.146
- Mm, when did he shave
his mustache?

14:57.229 --> 14:59.565
- Principal Pearson!

14:59.648 --> 15:01.984
- Yeah, we get it, Deb.

15:02.067 --> 15:04.820
- No! Principal Pearson!

15:04.903 --> 15:07.364
{\an3}- Principal Pearson,
what are you doing here?

15:07.448 --> 15:10.117
- I'm a member
of Celine on Me.

15:10.200 --> 15:12.536
You will all be held
accountable!

15:12.620 --> 15:16.957
- No. This was my idea,
and I refuse to be silenced.

15:17.041 --> 15:18.542
- Shush!

15:18.626 --> 15:21.170
You are all suspended!

15:24.089 --> 15:25.883
- He can't stop us!

15:25.966 --> 15:30.179
Look how many of us came out
to support this cause!

15:30.262 --> 15:32.723
Let the march begin!

15:32.806 --> 15:34.725
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:34.808 --> 15:36.769
{\an3}- All right,
it's about that time.

15:36.852 --> 15:38.520
Who's here for Trivia Night?

15:38.604 --> 15:40.356
[crowd cheers]

15:40.439 --> 15:42.691
{\an3}One minute, that way.
Have fun, guys!

15:42.775 --> 15:46.612
[crowd cheers]

15:46.695 --> 15:51.116
[banging on drum]

15:51.200 --> 15:52.201
- [gasps]

15:55.496 --> 15:58.999
<i>- ♪ Take down ♪</i>

15:59.083 --> 16:00.793
<i>♪ Take down ♪</i>

16:00.876 --> 16:03.671
- Ms. Cannon, your suspension
isn't up until Monday.

16:03.754 --> 16:06.298
- I'm so sorry to interrupt.

16:06.382 --> 16:08.217
But I've had time to think,

16:08.300 --> 16:10.219
{\an3}and I just wanted
to let you know I understand now

16:10.302 --> 16:12.721
{\an3}that the actions of the staff
do reflect on the school.

16:12.805 --> 16:14.306
- I'm glad.

16:14.390 --> 16:15.557
{\an3}- In fact, I've been
researching the activities

16:15.641 --> 16:17.351
of other staff members.

16:17.434 --> 16:18.602
- Good for you.

16:18.686 --> 16:21.939
{\an3}- I didn't realize that you
spent a year in clown college.

16:22.022 --> 16:23.357
- Yes, I did,

16:23.440 --> 16:27.403
in France, where it's considered
an art form.

16:27.486 --> 16:30.155
Now if you don't mind,
I'm busy.

16:30.239 --> 16:31.281
- I also saw a video of you

16:31.365 --> 16:33.909
{\an3}winning the 1987 quad-city
aerobics championships.

16:33.992 --> 16:38.747
- Yes, Olivia Newton-John
presented me

16:38.831 --> 16:40.833
with the Gold Headband.

16:40.916 --> 16:41.542
Is there anything else?

16:41.625 --> 16:43.877
- Actually, there is.

16:43.961 --> 16:46.171
{\an3}My friend Meadow, who I lived
in a yurt with in college,

16:46.255 --> 16:48.465
{\an3}works down
at the county courthouse.

16:48.549 --> 16:51.552
{\an3}And apparently in 1996,
you were arrested in Peoria

16:51.635 --> 16:54.430
{\an3}for publicly defecating
behind a Motel 6.

16:54.513 --> 16:56.974
{\an3}<i>I'm just here to offer</i>
<i>my support, Toby.</i>

16:57.057 --> 16:58.809
{\an3}I mean, I'd hate
to see you go down

16:58.892 --> 17:01.353
in this witch-hunt environment.

17:04.147 --> 17:08.234
And don't worry, I'll keep this
so no one gets a hold of it.

17:11.696 --> 17:14.700
- I lost my room key.

17:14.782 --> 17:18.494
- To Cecelia.
- Awesome.

17:18.579 --> 17:19.621
- You're a baller, girl.

17:19.704 --> 17:22.332
{\an3}- Yeah, thanks for getting
our suspensions revoked.

17:22.415 --> 17:23.416
{\an1}- I couldn't have done it
without you guys.

17:23.500 --> 17:26.795
{\an1}Now our personal lives
are nobody else's business.

17:26.878 --> 17:28.630
- Ah, thank goodness.

17:28.714 --> 17:31.175
It's like a weight has been
lifted off my shoulders.

17:31.258 --> 17:33.302
I've been living in fear
this whole week.

17:33.385 --> 17:36.722
- Why? What did you do,
Mary Louise?

17:36.805 --> 17:40.642
- What I'm about to tell you
needs to stay in this room,

17:40.726 --> 17:44.104
because if this gets out,
it will ruin me.

17:44.188 --> 17:46.148
- Oh, my God.
- What is it?

17:46.231 --> 17:47.941
- When I was in college...

17:48.025 --> 17:49.443
- Please let this be
a shit show.

17:49.526 --> 17:51.862
- I had
a nine-month correspondence

17:51.945 --> 17:54.656
with David Hasselhoff!

17:54.740 --> 17:56.158
[sobbing]

18:00.704 --> 18:03.290
<i>[opera music]</i>

18:03.373 --> 18:06.627
[cell phone ringtone]

18:06.710 --> 18:08.462
- [slurred] Hello?

18:08.545 --> 18:10.506
-<i> Ms. Snap? Principal Pearson.</i>

18:10.589 --> 18:12.925
<i>Your suspension</i>
<i>has been revoked.</i>

18:13.008 --> 18:16.178
<i>We need you back.</i>

18:16.261 --> 18:17.805
- Fill 'er up, cowboy.

18:17.888 --> 18:21.809
I'm about to get three more days
of vacation.

18:21.892 --> 18:22.935
Whoa--

18:23.018 --> 18:25.270
<i>[rock music]</i>

18:27.105 --> 18:30.067
